ide an\nefficient method for identifying these objects over large areas of the sky.\nBased on our success rate of 23 Halpha emission objects with spectral type in\nthe range M4-M7 out of 113 candidates with spectroscopic follow-up, we estimate\nthat there could be hundreds of such objects in the full IPHAS survey.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Oct 2008 12:06:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
